review_text: I love shopping at Petsmart for all my cat needs! This pet shop has everything you could possibly need in one place, making it super convenient. The staff is always helpful and friendly, which adds to the overall positive experience. Its my go-to pet store, and Im always happy with my visits.
Our pup Cali gets her haircut every couple months here.  5 Stars! Pet Smart Team communicates well and treats her great and haircuts looks awesome. Marcelle E cut Cali today 5/5 recommend!!!!
Its always a pleasure to stop at this Petsmart location. As soon you walk in, the cashier is happily greeting you and welcoming you.

Super polite staff, amazing with animals (big surprise), always a friendly face awaiting you. I can t speak highly enough of this team. Average prices, great and amazing selection. Generally go here for all my pet needs!

Friendly staff and a very clean store! The displays of the store are well thought out and the staff were very courteous and helpful! They also accept manufacture coupons here which is a great way to save a few dollars! Nice to see a wide variety of foods for your cats and dogs!

I was impressed by their customer service. You have the option to return the pet and anything you bought for the pet and get a full refund. No questions asked. That s what I call customer service. Thank you folks you made my day.
Able to find everything I need for my rabbit. Other pet stores lack exotic animal food and products. PetSmart has a great selection that caters to all critters.
This location is amazing, their small pet selection is so wide they have tons of merchandise that smaller petsmarts dont carry. Plus petsmart staff are always nice, no matter what location I go to

Was a very comfortable experience. Went to look for a cat stand with my daughter while my hubby went to shop for tools at another store nearby. They didnt have the stand, but they had cats up for adoption. Also, a lot of other  pets: guinea pigs, birds, fish... spent quite a bit of time admiring the animals. The staff was great. Didnt try to hard sell us or rush us.
There s a lot of choices  for my daughter s multi pooch . They have name engraving too! Amazing place .

This is the best pet smart location in the lower mainland. The staff really care about the animals here. They are so sweet and kind to them. I adopted a hamster, and two skinny pigs from this location. They made sure to gently pick up the hamster and didn t hold him on his back. Because they handled him so carefully he was a really sweet hamster and didnt bite us at all. In fact he would actually kiss us and lick our faces!  With the skinny pigs the employees recommend we buy two, so we did. They said good bye to them and put them in a large bin instead of a tiny box because they didnt want the skinny pigs to accidentally scratch each other. One is sassy and thick, and the other one is a cute gentle sweetie

I brought my border collie in to this location to be groomed, and cant say enough good things about Marcelle.    She did a fantastic job - the best of anyone weve had groom our dog.    This was our first visit to PetSmart for grooming, and we will definitely be back.   We hope Marcelle is still there next time we want to bring our dog in.    She was friendly, kind to our dog, and again, did a stellar job of the grooming.

My doggy really hates touching his nails. he bites whenever I try to cut his nails so i always failed to do that. However, Grommer Cassandra did the best so she made it today! Moreover, my dog looked so nice it was the best grooming ever! I will definitely go there again to let my dog get grooming service . Thank you Cassandra!
The best place for your pets needs. I cant say enough how grateful to have a place like this!

This has been our go to pet supply as everyone here is so nice and always helpful.  Our boy Rolo has become a recognized regular shopper and is always greeted with enthusiasm when we show up. We also take Rolo here for grooming specifically Danita as she is the only one who seems to be able to cut our boys nails (hes a little scared) she is always exceptionally caring for him and it is always a positive experience
Pet Smart shopping for our Birthday Puppers Einstein Good   Nice xtra small clothing, great food for our 4 pound Chihuahua   9 years young  Engraved tag/reflector

Ive got a little French Bulldog that the love store. She gets in there and wants to greet every client and every single person that works there she loves to have her way with the toys can you get free snacks she really likes the cat in the store as well.
Decent selection, organized. Prices are fair. Very nice, friendly and helpful staff.

We Took our dog Emma to the groomers for the time at pet smart apart from the gentleman at the front not saying hello how are you (Basic greeting) We have a awesome experience Emma was quite matted and they gave her a really nice short cut. We was in at 10.30 out by 12.00am!! We will be back
Great store! We took our dog in for some grooming and they accommodated us right away.
My go to pet store! Always so organized and staff like Colay are very helpful.
Love the rewards program and super friendly staff. Coley helped me out and is super awesome
Gateway you need very fast good customer service.

Prices are higher than any other option for pet stuff. But the staff who helped me was outstanding. She was well trained outside of PetSmart, very knowledgeable, and super helpful. Id shop there more even with the higher prices if all staff was as helpful as her. Tall, short white hair....     Thanks lady, sorry I didnt catch your name!
I took my dog to see Kelly T for grooming and I was so happy with result. Kelly was friendly, knowledgeable and great with my pup. Will definitely book with her again! Thank you.

but my hamster and rat there going back to buy my second rat there I find PetSmart on West 2nd and PetSmart on bento road are very different in their pet pick up policies as West 2nd seems to be more strict and bentall seems to be simple easier to get a pet I know at West 2nd you have to be there an hour before closing or they wont sell any pets to you and bento you can go 15 minutes before they close and they will still sell you a pet

My new puppy Bella (3 months) had her first puppy bath/ groom at this Pet Smart, last week- it was a perfect experience. The very professional staff took excellent care of my baby, put me at ease and she didnt even bark or whimper. She looked so clean and fluffy and smelled great. Great job groom team!
Great selection of dog foods anf super friendly staff who love their pets.  My dog lives coming in here (this is actually her rating because they took away her google account)
Im always very pleased with customer service. Trina helped me with my order. She was very friendly and efficient.I really appreciate her service
Great deals on aquarium starter kits!
Great selection and super friendly staff

Pretty good place to shop! I support them because the help with adoptions of pets ( ). Every time i go there, i make an additional donation for the charity they support. Selection of products is pretty good. I tend to buy Canadian brands, but they have quite a bit to choose from (domestic and US brands). Good sales, also! Free parkin!
Very friendly and professional staff . My dog loves going there !! Thats the best review for me :)
Has the best selection of cat food Ive seen so far in Vancouver. The area where they have cats for adoption looks appealing.

Friendly and helpful staff, very well organized. It s quarantine time, and they are all very considerate. Social distancing friendly. When there are animals available to see, they do not hesitate to let a customer visit. And everyone is very well taken care of! Also a very clean facility, with decent parking.
I was able to find what I needed quickly, with their organized aisles.
Always a pleasure shopping here.
Convenient location, friendly staff and the lines are never too long at this location. Parking is almost always available too.
The staff is so friendly and helpful in this store, I always like to return and buy what my pets need, from this place. They also have good discounts that are worth checking out.
Shopped there today as we have a new puppy joining our family. Had the pleasure of Abigail helping us choose food, a crate and treats. She was very knowledgeable which made for a great experience!

Very well stocked pet smart outlet. Lots of things that aren t available in Vancouver and online. I got a massive haul of stuff for my kitties. I especially like the range of natural cat litter options available. The staff are pleasant and plentiful parking options available in front of the store.
Able to get appointment for nail trim at this store while the closer one near downtown would not answer the phone.

Very friendly staff. Booked an appointment for my dog to be groomed and the process was very easy. I appreciate that they send text messages when your dog is ready for pick up and they also allow you to pay online beforehand. Great service

I bought two little guinea pigs from this location and the staff made sure I had the proper cage and food I needed for the babies. However after a week, i thought the babies might be sick and long story short, I was connected with Rob at this location and he was amazing. Despite their 14-day policy of only exchange or refund, when I was worried my piggies were sick, Rob made sure that my little piggies were checked and returned to me. Absolutely appreciate Rob s efficiency!

I walked in looking for a pet bed among other things, and thought I had found the pet bed section. There were about seven different models, each of sturdy construction and on average, atleast 20 bucks cheaper than the usual suspects (Rhymes with Slam Azon) Then a staff member, after asking if I needed help, politely informed me that those were just the ones on display, and showed me to a warehouse sized mecca of pet beds, taking up almost the entire rear of the store!! Holy Moses!! There were so many choices, it felt like choosing a new toothpaste/deodorant brand. I picked up a large dog bed and a topper for my sassy house cat and he actually loves it!  Hes a big stretcher, so a normal cat bed just didnt cut it. I would definitely recommend this store, the staff were friendly and helpful, and I found everything that I needed in one trip to one place.

Go see Cassandra for an amazing dog groom. She is fabulous every time, and super friendly. All the staff in the grooming department are lovely and I ve never had a bad experience in the two years we ve been bringing our dog here.

Staff here were so incredibly nice. I rented a carpet cleaner, and I had to buy a huge bottle of the liquid soap even though I only needed a tiny bit. So when I brought it back, I asked them to keep the bottle to give to the next person who took out a rental, to pay it forward. The guy took 50% off the cost of the soap because he felt bad I had had to buy such a huge bottle!!! It was so kind I got teary-eyed.
Bought a full tank of fish.  They have a 14 day satisfaction guarantee.   I brought 2 dead fishes and they let me do an exchange.   Willing to test my water for free as well.
Fish, dog, cats, rabbits, hamsters,..all the food and accessories
I like their selection of fish. This is my number one spot to get beta fish when the time is right. The workers there enjoy their job and make you feel welcome.

Linda, in the Pet area, fish mostly, is the best! She has helped me get a hamster, two fancy rats, and at least 50 or more fish...shes very knowledgeable, to the point and sweet! I always look for her when I go in!
Been here a few times and always had good service and friendly staff. I usually order online ahead of time before going to make sure they have the items for it s usually busy.
Trina is the best dog trainer. She is very enthusiastic about her job, and also extremely knowledgeable. She is very passionate and patience. I drive 45 min just to take her class with my dog.
Great customer service.  Sometime the product is out of stock! :(
Grooming service was amazing. My dog is very nervous and shy with strangers so they took their time with him. I appreciate it as the end result was great.

Beautiful visit at PetSmart today I have been buying my pet food at the veterinary for almost a year now at a higher cost then most so I thought why do I only have to go there they must have over weight management at pet smart too and they did I was so happy and saved a buck ur two as well so happy I checked it out and the bag of food is a upscale brand and a bigger bag.
Always friendly, helpful, and lots of coupons to earn!!
Friendly and helpful staff when getting a new furry pet hamster. Lots of accessories and snack options for hamsters.
Friendly and knowledgeable staff.

Has lots of stock on natural pet food brands and has a great adoption center that has furever pets looking for a lifelong home, that are adopted quickly. Good location, has a Starbucks, Canadian Tire, Save On Foods in the same complex.
Gary was very helpful for find out right product for my kitten. If you have any question(s), go for Gary.
Lots of free parking in the lot.  Sanitizer gels at entrance.  Helpful staff.  They were able to give me online discount because I wasnt able to sign on.  I went in person to buy instead.
Staff are friendly, always friendly ... and knowledgeable and genuine.  They care about pet care immensely

Totally love PetSmart we have two large cats and we went and bought the large cat harness week find and they didnt fit which we are allowed to return and then after we are also able to bring our cats to the store and a carrier we brought one cuz the other one doesnt like it and find a harness thats appropriate in the dog section for our cats really great service they also offer a card for I think points and they have kittens in the back and lizards as well as fish
The staff working in pet care are very helpful and knowledgeable! Great selection of local cat food and a large toy isle to wander through.

If you are a pet lover highly recommend you to visit this place, you can choice your pets favorite food from different brands, what is unique here is you also can adopt a lovely cat here, just between 175$ to 225$ with cash you can have a cat and bring it home very good situation and most of days you can find a lovely cat here for adopt, you also can buy several pets here like fish or hamester, birds and ect
Seems clean. Smells nice. Fish tanks are not so clean! Pet cages seem clean. There is normally someone able to help you and easyish to find. 4.9stars
Friendly staff. Cute hairstyle for my dog at always.
Great place for all your pet needs.  I like the shop online and pickup service.  Return/exchange policy is really great too.   Can usually find most things there.
I took my 2 corgis to the Bentall Street location - So much fun!! We picked out a couple of coats for them for the winter months ahead. Great price and staff and easy location with plenty of parking.

Love this store and after using a replacement groomer because PetSmart grooming salon was closed we will never let anyone other than Bernadine who treats Maggie with delicate hands. The substitute groomer left Maggie traumatized with nicks and red spots from shaver gauges.  Never again. PetSmart groomer a Bernadine forever.

This is now our go to place. PROS - They have a huge variety of pet food. Ample parking. All supplies for almost all pets. Grooming available and the best part, they have pet school (Lisa is amazing). CONS - none that I can think of.
Staff are very helpful. What we were buying was in sale when we got to the register the staff accommodated us quite quickly.
10/10 for Emma! Gave me a bag and was supa friendly

Has a great selection of supplies for many pets. Im always able to find my pugs favorite food. As well, enough supplies for my pet betta I recently bought from this store. Jerome (my betta) is looking great and is currently enjoying his new home!
Great store, friendly staff, never had an issue from this location
JUST GOT INTO THE FISH HOBBY AGAIN, AND ITS THE ONLY PLACE I GO TO FOR MY FISH. I PERFER BUYING WITH THE APP THEN SHOPPING INSTORE!.
Always come here to get my supplies. Everyone is so friendly. I like it when I get the friendly man as a cashier. Hes very polite and always asks about my dog
The grooming here is excellent and fairly priced.

Definitely my dog gets me to boost here, not my fault   she has these puppy dog eyes and she loves to distract the workers while I stuff my pockets with gear. I will however drop big bucks in the pet traveler and often drop 200 dollars here so cut me a break and let me steal the 30 dollar elk lpizzle
Adopted our first pet. Lots of great deals here and even better if you sign up for their points club. Bonus, they dont send you a card to carry around, just ask for your phone number.
Staff there are always knowledgeable and friendly.
Great customer service on the phone and in-person shopping. Was glad that an associate was able to direct me to the items I was looking for and answer any questions I had.

Employees in the rodent section were very knowledgable, and clearly care about the animals. Despite Petsmarts lacking care, its refreshing to see employees who value the wellbeing of the animals in store.
You can find everything for your pet here
The grooming is good and seems like a reasonable price. Some of their items you can get online for cheaper if you wait a day
Very clean location, the staff was helpful and friendly when approached. The prices are a bit high but in a pinch it s an easy in and out visit
The blue buffalo rep that was working here was super friendly and helpful when I was trying to find a chicken free soft kibble. FYI thats not a thing
Good quality food and other cat supplies. Everything we have bought here was well liked by our cat. Also the pet tag machine is phenomenal.
Great collection of everything you need for your pets, plus lways has something on sale.Staff are very kind and friendly.
My go to local pet store. Very friendly & helpful.  Recommend to anyone.
Great memories to go back to where we took our puppy to his first Puppy Class
Bought a beta fish, tank and all the necessities. Staff was very knowledgeable and helpful. We really appreciate all the advice.
This store has everything you need for any kind of pet.  Great service
The staff was very helpful and friendly. The associate Cassi (not sure on the spelling) was amazing and very knowledgeable, I would recommend this store to everyone.
Friendly and helpful staff
Staff are always friendly and helpful and very nice to the doggies :) gave my young puppy a large bone to help her stay in the cart comfortably
shout to Kelly in the salon! She made my pup look sooooo good and she was super kind too! Thanks Kelly !
Friendly staff, good supplies, and not busy at all. I visit every week go get feeder fish, and they always greet me when I come in!
Great products and prices and friendly staff. Dont forget to donate at the til and help save a life.
Pet smart gave me crabs lol

It s a good pet shop in comparison to other stores. Most of the products are well organized and you won t have hard time finding what you want. They provide a buzzer to ask for assistance which is quite satisfying, because I always struggle with finding a store associate to help me out. The store associate at Vancouver s west 2nd Ave are so helpful and kind.

Staff is always friendly and helpful. Seems like people that work their really enjoy their jobs. We took our dog here from her training. The trainer, Donna, is great. Very patient and always happy to see us. We take our dog here for a walk sometimes and always find new things to buy. They have pumpkin cookies for Halloween.

I ve been getting my Bernedoodle groomed by Michelle since she was a puppy and Michelle is FANTASTIC. The cut always looks good and she s very patient (my girl hates getting her face trimmed) Highly recommend the groomers, make sure you leave a tip. They re always busy and do a great job. Also very friendly staff.

Exceptionally friendly and accommodating staff, we were half an hour late to a kitten adoption meeting and the volunteer was still happy to meet with us. She even let us play with all the cats and got us an answer for all our questions.

Editing my review as I always come to this location for my dog s grooming and to pick up supplies. The staff here are amazing! Every time we walk by, my dog stands outside looking in with her tail wagging. We also did the intro puppy training course here and it was so cute when they gave out graduation hats on the last day.

Went in today for little fish, shrimp and some water plants. Peggy the store manager is very friendly and knowledgeable. She elaborated the tool we need and the some instructions. Very nice experience shopping there.
Excellent service, my dog is always happy when he goes to PetSmart!
Friendly staff good location with spa and training services. Underground parking available.

Woohoo    Petsmart thank you    for the bird   box   and the bird   hospital    . We haven t made it yet but we put blue    in the small cage separately from the other two birds   for now let him have some space
Had a lovely experience, Rose here helped us check out asked us about our day our experience we shared our adoption story with them/him/her.
Great location, always has what we need. Love the Treats program too!
Fantastic small store but has everything you need. The staff are very friendly and have helped me choose various products for my new pup Winston!
Really big pet store and has all the pet food you may want to have... Many brands..liked the stock.. can go for anything you want, wont be disappointed..
Cindy, the cashier was excellent. She was fast, knowledgeable, and polite. She deserves a bonus!
Always go there. Downside: parking! Othereise, worth every time you go there when you feel bored or need something for the lovely pet!
Great location, awesome customer service from all staff including management. My dog Parker loves going there!

Great location with excellent staff who are attentive, courteous and respectful. The cashier was particularly helpful. They have good prices overall on just about anything. Also, their return policy is fantastic. If youre not satisfied for any reason, a return is hassle-free. Pet Smart parking is located underground entering on the side street.

They have their Betta fish in giant tanks and they are so happy! The best price on guppies and ghost shrimp and aquarium plants. Service here is always fantastic (sometimes slow but whatever, its a giant shop!) and they have a huge variety of everything you could ever need to ensure you have the happiest pets. Excellent selection of dog and cat food, toys and costumes! I really love this store and always get everything for my pets.

The puppy training class at this location is very good, especially with Donna as the trainer.  Location is clean and convenient to get to by walking from yaletown. Perfect distance to get our puppy warm up before class. Toy and treat selection was good, employees were friendly and helpful.

Every time I come, I have nothing but a positive experience! A little bit of a crammed store in my opinion, especially compared the one in Richmond that I visit often. But the staff are super friendly, everything that I look for is in-stock majority of the time, and theres great selection on pet products. Probably my favourite PetSmart!

Pet smart is a  favorite pastime for  my 9 month old puppy. We signed up for training classes the group class wasnt working out for my shy  puppy PetSmart offered an upgrade to attend a private class for a one on one training session.  I highly  recommend a private training  class for puppies.
This place is cool! Staff iz amazing. PetSmart has some great cupons system. You guys should check it
First time grooming my morkie with Yoshiko, loved how pretty and clean she was. I highly recommend this place

Staff here are friendly. Theres alot of variety of food treats etc. However if you have an XS or small dog the clothes are very limited and not the greatest of selections. Otherwise its pretty good store for all your pet needs.
Nice store, friendly staff, large selection of all things pets.

Their training and grooming services were absolutely great. The price is super reasonable. My dog has a serious anxiety problem and when I took him a different grooming salon, I had to give him a calming drug but still hold him down so tight while he was freaking out  however this place was the first place he had his nail cut done by himself. I was so scared of being refused because of his aggression while waiting outside but the trainer went to check how he was doing for me between her lessons(I guess that was on her break). That made me feel safe and comfortable.  Thank you so much for all helps. This is the only grooming place Ill take him.
Good, clean location with knowledgeable staff. Small but compact for pet essentials compared to other locations. Great none the less. I wish they groomed cats but that s okay.
Parking is in the side of the building can b validated with purchase in store. Michelle & Camilla groom my pups beautifully every time.  & the points are great to get

Conveniently local close to cambie bridge. Store is massive with everything you need for whatever pet you may have. They also offer pet training classes on site. I recently found out they have parking downstairs which you will be validated for when paying for goods. They staff are friendly and very knowledgeable. You can also take your pet dog or cat with as it is pet friendly.

This location can feel a little busy because its a smaller store, but if you go later (in the hour or two before closing) theres a good chance youll be the only customer there. Helpful, really nice staff. Free underground parking as long as you show them your parking ticket (they deduct the price of parking from your purchase).
Fun lots of fish and wide variety of tanks and foods for petts mostly cats dogs fish birds and reptiles fish was my main focus of going. Pretty cool. Very competitive prices
Clean facility. Kind and helpful staff. The small pets look healthy as well which is a large indication of a good pet store. Bring your doggies for a treat!

I took my rescue dog here for his first grooming appointment. He was matted with almost ingrown nails. They were nothing except gentle with him even though he tried to bite them. He looks like a different dog. Very thankful for the kind groomers here.

I am writing this review because of the excellent customer service I received while shopping there today.    I normally dont shop here because its not in my neighbourhood,   but saw it while driving by and decided to check it out.    The service employee,   Chris,   went above and beyond to help me find products,    and he found an on sale I needed,   but didnt see.   Chris was very patient,   calm,   knowledgeable,   and is an example of what customers like myself appreciate when  shopping,   especially in a big box store.    I also liked their wide selection of products,    and their prices are not any more expensive than other pet supply stores.    Thank you,   Chris.    I hope the Petsmart management recognize and value your contribution to customer service,    its employees like you who help me  decide to shop there again.    Thank you !

I dont typically write reviews for larger corporations - but this location and its management are absolutely WONDERFUL. Laura, specifically, was so incredibly kind, accommodating, and displayed so much empathy and integrity. This branch is incredibly fortunate to be under such great management.

Highly recommend the dog training classes with Eva! My beagle puppy is like a new dog after the 4 weeks of training. Most importantly, I know how to train him properly going forward. Eva was amazing, Archie will miss her dearly until we return for Advanced Classes in a couple of months!
Great customer service. Easy parking.
Excellent experience every time I shop here. Great prices and access to products we rely on. Staff are knowledgeable and helpful. I feel appreciated and value as a customer when I shop here.
Great selection, friendly staff

Im a new fish owner! In a series of interesting circumstances- I acquired some big fish   and so my tank was having some issues (one fish mysteriously died)... The lady cashier was super helpful, and helped me diagnose the situation just by listening to my explanation. She even double checked the fish medicine I was getting, and gave me some guidance. I really appreciate the genuine and caring service that I received! Thank you so much!

This location is always a pleasant experience, especially when dealing with Peggy, the manager. She recently helped us with a return/exchange which would ve normally been a huge headache but she was a total rockstar about it and was very helpful! We will keep returning to this location because of her. Highly recommended. Kudos to you, Peggy!
Went for grooming services. My dog had a bath here. He seems to have enjoyed himself. The staff are friendly, the prices are relatively affordable.
staff went out of their way to be extra accommodating and helpful for my dog and I. The store always has a ton of variety and pretty good sales!

Always so friendly. Also, I may be mistaken, but I believe PetSmart carries most, if not all, of the Wellness brand of cat and dog foods. My cat has decided its Wellness Select or nothing... Its not cheap, but given that the rest of the prices here are in line/competitive enough with other majors in the industry, I dont blame PetSmart for that. I blame the fabulously wealthy people who clearly whisper in my cats ears about all the things he deserves when Im not looking.

I give the staff, selection & prices 5-stars. The issue below has been addressed  & I have added the star that was held back. XoXo Previous Review: The poor interior lighting coupled with small font sizes on packages (& shelf price labels) unduly increases time spent to check ingredients before buying your pet a new treat. It is fatiguing. If this negative value is addressed I believe it would translate into more sales as customers will be inclined to look at more products. XoXo

Totally amazing. Got my hamster Timby today, I m leaving him be in his enclosure until he is comfortable enough to let me tame him. Jake was amazing, super gentle and very nice. Made sure I knew what I was doing and was prepared before taking him home. Totally recommend.
You can find what ever you want aaaaand the staff in VAN :)
Awesome variety and lovely customer Service
Great and knowledgeable service. Thanks guys!
The sales rep was very helpful and polite. I will definitely be shopping there again for my hedgehog supplies
Always as a good stock variety and availability. Click and collect really quick and easy. Staff are always happy and helpful. My dog loves the free snacks at the register.
I always got treat and hay for my bunnies there
Helpful staff, good selection, and theres always cute dogs wandering in the store. Located in a trendy neighbourhood with good restaurants and coffee around.

Came in a couple weeks ago to get my dog some oral hygiene products and couldnt be more happy. I went to 2 other pet stores before coming here and couldnt find the specific treat my dog actually appeals to. I came here and after searching the entire store I was just about to walk out until I decided to check with the clerk and she walked me over to the exact treats my dog likes and told me they were very new so they had the display up front. Anyways, I couldnt be happier! I bought a small bag of Arcs naturals and now my dogs horrible breath is slowly getting better. She WILL NOT eat any other dental treat, these are the best, I definitely recommend. Thank you.

Bought a reptile tank from here. Upon bringing it home we found a large crack in the side. With how the tank was packaged it would have been impossible for staff (or us) to see it in advance. Gave them a call and they said they had no replacement, but could call us when one came in. Sure enough, 4 days later we received a call. Went in to pick it up and Matt was extremely accomodating, he carried the cage right over to us and made the transaction happen seamlessly. They handled an unavoidable, unfortunate situation with professionalism and compassion, well done!

I go to this store for the selection, 2 huge aisles each of cat and dog food.  Plus lots of fish and bird things too.  The location is just a short block walk from the skytrain.  The prices could make you weep, so all I can say on that note, is that the prices everywhere else seem to be just as bad, if not worse, which is also why I go there.  The toy selections are really good too. Very pet friendly, of course, I always meet a new dog friend or 2 when I go there.  Also, the cashier was very funny when I accidentally handed her the competitions savings card instead of the PetSmart card.  Said it happens all the time.   It took me about 15 minutes to spend $52 on cat food, half wet (cans), half dry.  My girl is a very happy kitty   tonight! She keeps going back to her dish for more kibble,  like every ten minutes.  I may have to ration her severely.   CHEERS everyone, love your furry friends, they so deserve it.
The staff are always professional and knowledgeable. Could have been 4.5 stars because their cat grass quality is quite random.
Good selection , plenty of food and toys , cages ect , prices are reasonable... Will continue to shop here ..
Got ourselves a frog for the BEST BUY at Cambie. But I think it broke after a while and decided to be a Bat

Awesome customer service. Theyre always super attentive. Today I had one of the customer service reps tell me that Orchard Hay was essentially the same as Timothy Hay and theres no difference, but my bunny doesnt like it at all    Apparently she can tell the difference.
Staff is very professional and helpful :)
Everyone is super friendly! We go here weekly with our puppy and he just loves it. We also completed their puppy training class with Victoria (she s awesome) and found it very helpful!

A lady who assisted was so kind and friendly. However, we are keep coming back here for shrimps for our aquarium thinking they will replenish as they say, but they only have one variety left. We just bought them anyway. Accessible by Canada line and busses.
We bring our puppy here for grooming and they re incredible! They do wonderful work and they re all so loving with the dogs. Kayla S was especially great if you can book with her!

I love this PetSmart! The staff are always so friendly and talkative - always willing to offer help and chat about our respective pets (or pet prospects). I love that they change their selection up so often and their return policy is really great as well. Thanks!
Good vibes. Been here a couple times with my hedgehog and friends dogs. They enjoyed their visit each time. Nice and helpful staff as well!

Incredible customer service at this location. I was helped out by Matt the other day. I made a mistake (chicken) with the puppy food I purchased and he gave me a full credit. They were currently out of the food (beef) bag size I was after but he took the time to let me know when it would be restocked. Introduced me to the Merrick rep who happen to be in house and also took the time to interact with my pupper, which only helps with his socialization. Just wanted to say a big Thank you to Matt and his team. They always take good care of us there.

They have the cutest little pet toys! The frog makes frog noises and the two little mice are the most adorable toys i have ever seen. My ferrets instantly approved them by stealing them from coffee table, before i had a chance to remove the packaging.

The online grooming was very easy and the wash and cutting my dog nail was great, I had another service booked and they told me it was not necessary . So it end up cheaper than what I expected. Good job.
The staff is always friendly and helpful. Their inventory is always good, I can always find what I m looking for and their cue side pick-up is great! They also validate your parking!
Good selection of products and helpful people. They were out of what I wanted, but these days you cant always blame a store for that.

I try to buy my dog supply here. Their prices are abit high, but the offer training classes which is really helpful and also they have 100% lively and supportive staffs. I try different branches and everywhere i went they were so helpful and friendly.
Lots of variety of products, reasonable prices, prompt and pIeasant service.  Great place to shop.
I love all the people working here, they re so lovely w put pets

We just adopted a fantastic little guy from Vancouver Cat Therapy & Rescue, the organization partnered with PetSmart. They were fantastic to deal with. The staff at PetSmart knew all about our little guy and were really helpful with getting us set up to get our new addition home and had great offers for new pet parents.

Well stocked, clean pet supply store close to transit services. My interest, plentiful aquarium livestock in clean, healthy tanks -many fish varieties, shrimp, snails and more. Some freshwater plants. Good number of aquarium parts and supplies in stock- pumps, lights, water quality supplies, tanks, decorations and much more!

Best place for pet foods that we found. Service is decent too, with good hours and overall convenience. Delivery option is a good add on, but they used FedEx, which is meant for businesses, and not good for residential addresses so thats something I hope PetSmart fixes. Canada Post would be much better for customers since if we miss delivery, its easy to go pick it up at a post office near by, while FedEx doesnt have that option and you cant tell what time of day they will try to deliver.
Nice clean store lots of things for puppies and kittens. We bought a really nice new bed for our puppy dog and he loves it. The staff are friendly

I used to buy most of my pet products in the U.S. until Pet Smart opened stores in the lower mainland. Selection is good and prices are better than the boutique pet stores. Pet Smart even carries BC brands like True Leaf in their stores. I was disappointed when Pet Smart discontinued their Equisicate corn litter. It was my favorite after trying over 20 different litter brands.

Every time I ve been there I ve received excellent service! Everyone seems to be quite knowledgable on fish which is why I continue to go there when I am unsure or need something for my aquarium. If you bring a sample of your aquarium water they will even test it for you and tell you if it s healthy or what you might need to make it better.
I love this location. The staff is always super friendly and helpful. My dog loves coming here. For the size of the store the selection is decent.

Always friendly, helpful and knowledgeable staff. Great that I can return items if my dog doesnt like them without question. Convenient location. Clean store. Plethora of items to choose from. Prices compatible to other pet stores.

We have been going to see Dana at the grooming salon since Pepe was a baby. He is a medium size Maltese, 3 Years old full of energy. The only problem is that Dana is so amazing that is hard to get an available time in her schedule

Barbara is a cat whisper.  The very best groomer ever!  She takes such good care of our cat and gives the best haircut ever!  Our cat is not the easiest, so we were told from the other groomers but not with Barbara.  When I came into the store to pick her up, Barbara was holding her in arms.  Amazing!  I hear she is leaving to Richmond store.  So not fair.

PetSmart is well-located and has free underground parking. The large selection of products at a competitive price plus a knowledgeable and friendly staff make shopping there a pleasant experience. There especially geared for cats and dogs.

Great grooming!! We took our dog here for an impromptu groom as we are visiting from out of town, though get our dog groomed at our local PetSmart. Shonte was our dogs groomer and she did an AMAZING job. Ears to tail and everything in between, its evident she cares about the work she does as Ive never seen a more even groom. I would highly recommend bringing your pets here for a cleanup!
The woman helping me in the fish department seemed to really know her stuff.
Good selection of dog food and treat. If you are a member, you can also save some money and collect points.
Great grooming service by Michelle! Jasper loves his new haircut and he smelled sooo good. Highly recommend the puppy trim for puppies that are new to grooming.

Great sales on a lot of their doggie products, most importantly the staff made our newly adopted pupper feel much more comfortable coming in. I cant speak to their in house training as we havent tried it but I think we will soon!

We went to this location to get a heat light for our turtle, and found Erika to be very helpful and knowledgeable in the specific needs of our pet. We will definitely come back if we need to shell out for any more supplies in the future!

I was buying dog food since my dog was having digestion problems. I went to buy another food formulated for my yorkie puppy specifically, the associate there read the ingredients of what I chose and educated me on the stuff you dont want in your dog food. So she recommended something else formulated for dietary sensitive puppies and now my puppy is feeling amazing. And because of this we were able then house train our puppy properly now. Complete game changer. Thanks to that female associate (sorry I didnt get your name).
Good pet shop where you can find many options about food, beds, toys, grooming, etc...

Took my pupper for his first-ever grooming session. He s usually anxious with new people and new situations   but I think I was the more anxious one! Michelle was his groomer for the day, and she was so sweet putting my dog (and me) at ease. He had the full package   a haircut, his nails clipped, a bath... all of the above + some extras. When I picked him up, Michelle gave me some tips & tricks on what I can do to make his next appointment easier (i.e. she said he didn t like his chin being touched, so I should train him to make him comfortable with that). That was super helpful! And despite the fact that we re still in Phase 2 of Covid-19, and they re not allowed to have 2+ stylists on a dog (for their physical distancing safety), Michelle still did a really good job with my dog s nails solo. I would definitely recommend this location and Michelle as a stylist to anyone.
Took my very nervous for to have her nails trimmed. The store associates were so great!
The wife has 2 cats 1 has a sensitive stomach pet smart sells blue buffalo sensitive stomach so I went with her to get it here

Theycan  have more pet things than I imagined existed ANYWHERE!! No they dont pay me .. Or anything else.free cat food? Nah they could and I would maybe accept but what could I say thats true and better? If you like animals go in when you are passing a PS store.. Cool..and some of the employees are too ..if yer clerk isnt what you want jus loom about and pick again ..too bad my apt doesnt have room for a ton of cages and habitats .grin c for yourself and let me know if wrong..cheers
Have been taking our dog to get groomed here for many years. She always looks great and enjoys her time with the groomer.
I took my 4 month old for a puppy trim. Yoshiko did a great job, paid attention to details and my pup came out fresh and clean and happy! Thanks again
Friendly and approachable staff. Curb side pick-up was quick and easy. Also, shout-out to Love who rectified an issue with my order.

One stop shopping, very exciting to visit when youre in love with your pets. Very spacious, clean and well arranged, a lot of foods, treats, toys, clothes, accessories, and other stuffs for your pets. As far as I noticed, they cover dogs off course, cats, fish, birds, reptiles, and other small pets (like rabbits, hamster, guinea pigs, even rats and mice). Although I never used their service, but hard to miss that they also have grooming and training facilities. For the clothes, I found not too many choices, but for food and treats they have quite a lot options to choose. Installing their phone apps is worth it, where we can find promotion info, check stock availability, online shop, book appointment for services, etc. For Petsmart, keep up the good job!

Being here to get my new fish tank. I ordered a open top fish tank branded as top fin. It costed me $189 before tax. Filters, temperature controller, oxygen bar, and some more equipment. I spent another $200 on that. $4.99 per each fish. Got 30 fiahes but actually give me 28 fishes. Died 5, I have 23 left in a 40 gal tank. After spending so much money and effort on the new tank, we finally got a well-set fish tank. Perhaps, I have to get another 20 fish next time.
I love this store! Every time I go the staff is so friendly and helpful. I definitely one of my favorite pet stores because of the great customer service and great finds!

Big THANK U for pet grooming salon team! Every time when my French Bulldogs go to do nail trim or full bath they always treat them with love and patient! I can feel they really cares my dogs. Their Rewards program is worth to join as well, you can get coupons and points to redeem for cash.
Very nice &  friendly staff, the cashier was able to solve my need
Great selection.   Easy to find what looking for.  Associate Hannah was friendly helpful and most of all knowledgeable

Friendly staff. Great for fish a day fish needs. I took my pup in there to get a treat, he loves to walk around and say hi to other dogs, I check for sales, they have a lot of stuff but not always the cheapest. They offer grooming services as well.
The kittens favourite place! They really do have anything for pets! Staff is friendly, the place is organized and prices seem reasonable.

Masae and Mimi are salon pros. With over 10 years of grooming experience, they re especially good with mats. Our labradoodle leaves with a perfect furcut / blowout style every time! Thank you for your service!

As I waltzed into Pet Smart with my shopping list in hand, I couldnt help but feel a sense of excitement bubbling up within me. On my quest for 11 neon tetras, dog food, and other pet essentials, I was prepared for a whirlwind of an experience. And let me tell you, dear readers, Pet Smart did not disappoint! The moment I entered, I was greeted by a symphony of meows, barks, and the gentle swish of fish swimming in their tanks. Like a seasoned conductor, Pet Smart had orchestrated a harmonious blend of products and services to cater to a wide array of pets and pet parents alike. With my eyes set on the aquatic section, I was pleasantly surprised by the variety of fish on display. The neon tetras, in particular, caught my attention. They shimmered like tiny aquatic gems, boasting vibrant hues of red and blue. With the help of an attentive staff member, I handpicked 11 of these underwater dazzlers to take home to my own aquatic kingdom. Next on my list was dry and wet dog food, and Pet Smarts selection was nothing short of a canines dream buffet. From grain-free options to high-protein and even gourmet choices, the variety was extensive and tail-waggingly delightful. I managed to find the perfect balance of nutrition and flavor for my furry companion, leaving me feeling like a true doggy connoisseur. As for the other supplies, Pet Smart offered a plethora of options for both fish and dogs. From aquarium filters and heaters to leashes and chew toys, I found myself lost in a maze of pet care nirvana. The stores organization and knowledgeable staff made navigating through this treasure trove of pet supplies a breeze. In the end, my experience at Pet Smart was akin to a tango with my beloved pets - a dance of delightful discoveries and well-executed moves. With a cart filled to the brim with neon tetras, dog food, and other essentials, I couldnt help but feel grateful for this one-stop pet utopia. Pet Smart, you have truly outdone yourself, leaving this pet parent more than satisfied and ready for an encore. Bravo!

Ive always found what I needed there. Pretty much has everything you need for your pets. Staff are always welcoming and helpful when needed, as its a big store and a bit harder to find specific items. They have good options for fish and birds, and few lizards and hamsters as well.
It s a good place reasonable prices and if they don t have what you need there more than willing to order it in for you.
Wow great stock of all my items for my new kitty. We live down the road from this place and will shop there again. Staff was very friendly
Easy to find what you need, fairly well stocked, adorable cats up for adoption as you enter. This place is awesome. Also, theres seldom more than 2 or 3 people in line here! Quick in and out.
Always had good experiences here, nothing out of the ordinary. Nice selections, clean store, friendly staff.

The staff at this location seem to genuinely care about the welfare of the animals. I ve had a few interactions with them and all seem reasonably knowledgeable in the different departments as well. It s reassuring to know they re not just there to do a job but also have concerns for the living conditions of the reptiles, amphibians, and small mammals
Well stocked wide variety selection of pet needs. Very tidy store. Sometimes sold out of live bugs.

This PetSmart has a number of kittens to adopt, on top of having a large store, a great selection of pet-related items and various small pets. We submitted a form to adopt one of these kittens, and a few days later someone called us to come in and pick her up. She was 15 weeks old and a happy squeaker. Our Cats, before they got spayed and neutered had a kitten together and raised it, so we were hoping they would adopt Miley as their own - and after less then 24 hours the new family has already bonded. Miley seems very happy here and in-between the cuddling she loves to run around and explore the place. Shes also very affectionate and loves to eat. We would recommend PetSmart if you are considering adopting a kitten.

PetSmart is one of my go to place for dog accessories, shampoos, and toys. Staff are generally helpful. When you have an account and make purchases you can accumulate points to go towards future purchases. Sometimes they have great sales and I end up spending more than I originally planned. Well played, PetSmart, well played.
Great place for your pets stuff.  Staff is friendly and helpful.  Great environment.
Friendly staff, good selection of pet items
I was very happy with the service PetSmart provided. The staff was knowledgeable, accommodating, and gentle to my dogs. I was very satisfied with the outcome.

This is one of the longest serving pet stores in the region. Its located in a small strip mall along with a dollar store and the golf town. Across the street is Michaels craft store and Tim hortons. Theres also a sun given foods grocery store in the same parking lot. Thats actually the most challenging part of attending this store is the parking which can be quite busy. Otherwise the store is great because its so large and serves all types of pets from dogs and cats to small mammals, fish and reptiles as well. Of course they have food for all these types of animals which is great because we have a snake and are always looking for a local supplier. The store is always clean and not too busy period they have grooming services as well as dog training services. There is a had adoption centre at the front of the store. There seems to be enough staff that work here to provide a good customer experience overall. Value for money is what you would expect at a pet store and overall the experience is excellent. Definitely will come again.
The staff there are very friendly and helps you find anything you need. And you can find everything you want in the store. There is also a pet salon inside of the store.
Awesome time there , cats dogs birds fish Meowwwww
Great location Easy parking Good service

Super friendly staff. Ordered online took less that 5 minutes to pick up and leave store. Great parking and easy to get to from Vancouver . And if you are looking for an adorable kitty they are here!!
Helpful staff and generally have what I need for my kittens. They also have fun seasonal stuff for pets, like for Halloween!
The facility is world class.  Its the old 2010 Winter venue, so it is a must visit and experience.  The staff are great too.  The climbing wall is an awesome sport to try out too
THAY HAD THE CUTEST RATS!!! Got 2 more to add to the mischief. Great staff, they were very kind and helpful.

This store is the greatest! The staff are super friendly and knowledgeable plus their grooming is fantastic!! My fur baby is 11 years old now and HATES when we try and bathe her yet pet smart is able to get her looking beautiful every time :)) thanks a bunch!!

Always have the things I want ofc. I take my dog grooming every couple months and Crystal is my groomer, she is really kind and through and lets me know what she will do before dropping my dog off. She is very professional and knows how to make my pupper looks handsome at the end of the groom!
Good selection for a variety of pets. Staff are helpful.  Love the online shopping and pick up in store option. Allows you to see if the item(s) you need are in stock.

It was the first time I was bringing my sheltie in for a wash. Everything was simple and easy. They send you appointment reminders the days leading up and easy check in s online. I booked with Irene and she did an amazing job, my dog was so clean and fluffy. Would definitely go back!

so I ordered something online with a $10 giftcard. I threw away the gift card after the purchase as I didnt expect the order would be cancelled. I had to call in to see how they can help. The call got connected pretty quick and they gave me another $10 gift card and refunded my points for the purchase. Everything was done smooth and quick.

Having a pup and kitty Im at this store frequently. Ive also used the grooming salon here. Id say the staff in the store are very well educated about animals. I wasnt sure of the correct puppy food and spoke with a staff member and she gave me alot of good info and advice. The salon did an awesome trim and gave me a record of what services were performed on coco. From that Its easy to keep track of what you are paying for and what needs to be done next time. All in all a great store for everything!

Good store compared to the Vancouver one. Very well lit place and kind cashier who cared for the cat being housed at the store. I prefer coming to this branch as its quite wide selection for many small pet items.

Way above my expectations. There was this girl who was extremely helpful, giving extremely honest feedback that I greatly appreciated. Im a dog owner to be and her suggestions were honest, more like an owner to owner advice, than a sales associate advise. I would definitely go back there many times.

I was searching for a small fish tank and needed some help.  There were a lot of customers due to a sale but I approached after only a short wait.  Then while I was comparing tanks I accidentally dropped one and cracked it.  I was mortified.  The sales agent was so nice.  As i kept apologizing she just inspected, moved it off to the side and told me not to worry. Yes some prices are higher but they offer good hours, good range of supplies, price matches and Ive never been hung up on like I was for another pet store.  (Mr) They also have online inventory of in-store stock for some items.  If only they had it for all their items.
Brought my 6-month-old puppy in to get his nails dremeled. Krystal did such a great job I highly recommend her. Thank you so much krystal for taking such good care of tofu
I like this PetSmart. I had my dog take lessons here. Staff are friendly and helpful. I ve always been able to find what I need for my dog here and it is relatively close to home. Thank you PetSmart!
Great place to get all sorts of pet food.

Sidney is an amazing groomer, so sweet, she does an excellent job every time I bring my dog there (who has a VERY difficult kind of coat to groom). They always let me know how he was when i go to pick him up! excellent customer service

Always nice to visit this store. Friendly staff. clean environment. My son loves to say hi to each of the pet up for adoption. We just love learning about their stories and pray that each one gets a loving home.

Very knowledgeable,super friendly staff to seem to be working very hard.. I find that normally they seem to be somewhat under staffed.. that goes for each of the locations I have visited in the past.   This is not any fault of the staff in place during any of my visits to all locations in metro Van.  I guess one could almost suggest that they appear to be somewhat over worked ..just my outside opinion.

Crystal did a spectacular job taking care of my long-haired (double-coated) Chihuahua.  He looked great and he was obviously very happy.  Crystal also made sure to review the service with me and read over the online notes i made when booking the appointment. I look forward to returning in the New Year.

Great experience at this Petsmart! Great selection of toys and treats for my dog. Super friendly service from the staff. Even kind enough to call me a cab and let me use her phone. Nice place to shop and get advice.
Excellent service. The staff member didn t know the answer to my question but went in the back to check stock and brought me what I needed. Very helpful!

Just got my puppy recently so i decided to get some essential items. I was pretty clueless what to get until the staff there. The store had a huge selection but I was here for my dogs grooming. Came about 2 months ago and my Maltese poodle had a groom with Emily. Loved the haircut! She did a really good job

Our dog was always terrified of getting her haircut, but the terror has subsided since we started taking her to the salon here. The groomers are exceptionally kind and competent. So relieved that we found them!

Just visited their grooming salon based on a friends recommendation. Masae (the groomer) was super friendly and I could tell that she loved animals and loved grooming them. She took the time to understand the style I wanted for my bichon and the results were great!

Needed to get some wild birdseed and I called in and a girl was unbelievably helpful, knowledgeable and helpful. I didnt catch her name but thank you for all your help and info! My lil tweet tweets are happy happy happy and so am I.

Friendly staff with a great selection of toys for your pet who are always welcome. They have an excellent training program and in house grooming. Clean bathrooms with a pet friendly atmosphere. Pet smart does it right.
Best pet store in all of Richmond! Carries everything you need and the staff are very knowledgeable. I also love to order online and pickup in store! Makes for quick and easy shopping!
This is for the grooming service. After trying several different groomers, Masae here, is the best! Clearly loves dogs and her job.
Great place clean friendly
Kids love seeing the reptile and kitten.

Every time I go to Petsmart, I love thr atmosphere and friendly staff. Although the shelves are empty but I am managed to find what I need

Very friendly knowledgeable staff.  Our puppy had an ear infection and the young man was able to help us out.  Puppy is happy, so are we :)

Staff is extremely cooperative every time I visit this place. There is no hurdle in getting anything returned if we have to. In addition to that, huge collection of pets and accessories to choose from.
Large amounts of cats and dogs food selection on a lower price. Fishes, birds, and bugs for sell. Cats for adoption in the front. Staff seems friendly. Been going there for a number of years now.
The place looks very neat and orderly.the staffs are very helpfull and you can feep that they always have a warm smile underneath that mask
Went there for buying treats and collar for my new puppy. Pet trainer is very friendly and give us a lot of great info regarding on grooming and training!

Just about everything you could ever need.  Urgently needed a ramp for my dog post surgery and I was thrilled at what I was able to find - it was exactly what I wanted and cost less than the same item, used on Craigslist.
great selection on cat litter products. great prices

This is where we go to get food and litter for the cats. They usually have good sales if you have the members points card. They have a spot for cats that you can adopt. Its nothing special. Its a PetSmart.
Stop by to get some treats and toys for Cleo. Selection is always great. Not too many people so no line ups at all.

6 yes ago i got a crab and still well and alive . Thanks petsmart
I love it but its too good sometimes they stop you from doing what you think is right but is wrong other wise its the total best in Richmond.
Staff are always friendly and helpful at this location.
Staff at this location seem to change quite a bit, but they are all still very helpful and knowledgeable. Had my puppy trained here at their puppy training courses and it was very useful!

A big store with almost everything you need for your little family member. They provide classes for dogs in store. The service of adoption is also provided at the entrance. They also have fish to sell at the back.
Good hours wide range of pet supplies staff is very friendly and one of the last retailers to actually help with your purchase to your vehicle
I love coming here at night to pick up live pet food. Always fast service.  Nice and quiet too
Great price and inventory got what we wanted and shout out to Natasha for helping my nephew
Might not be a big Petsmart with many selections but Great & very friendly staff. One of my ducks favorite places to get her treat worms from!!!!!
Friendly staff that are knowledgeable who are pet lovers and owners. Large store with plenty of selection and competitive prices. Lots of parking and close to the highway.
Our cat has had 3 hair cuts and spa treatments. The grooming staff are awesome.
Went for Chameleon food. The worker was really knowledgeable and polite, also so tall that I lost my train of thought because standing next to him threw me off lol.

Its great if you have a lot of Pets...lol , I have 2 dogs a cat, birds fish and a turtle and a Partridge in a pear tree

Joseph the dog trainer at this store is very knowledgable. The classes are very informative. I look forward to the next one. .
I come in every six weeks to get my dog s nails clipped. Excellent service every time.

Great customer service, Sophie was an amazing help with advice and suggestions on what kind of a terrarium to purchase, how to decorate it and keep the eco system habitable. Amazing and a friendly bunch of  grooming staff. Brought in my 15 month old Samoyed for a full grooming the 1st time and he looked and smelled fabulous! Ive been back a 2nd time already. Great job! Thank you
Thanks Sarah! LARRY loves his new cut!
Nice staff/associates there. Clean and well organized aisles. You can found almost all the things you needed for your pet.
Hello, my kitten really likes this store, it has really good quality pet food and furniture here.

Helpful staff and organized shelves.  Reasonable prices.  Playing the game on the app, you can earn 10%, 15%, and 20% off coupons on one item, which can be stacked with other promotions.  Overall, it was a pleasant experience.
I adopted willy boi, William this week with the help of pet smart and crtc

Came here with my cocker spaniel for a few grooming appointments. Once for a wash with Matthew, once for a trim with Jade and two days ago for a sanitary trim with Julie. I regrettably took him somewhere else for his last groom, a mistake which I will not be making again. I will be back to Petsmart for his next full groom before we move cities. Thank you!
We got to a beautiful Betta, and the whole set up for around 45$ but they have a wide selection of fish and accessories,they have pretty much anything for fish and their matentience .
Aline did an amazing hair cut and nail trim on my little fur baby. 100% recommend her!

Perfectly sized location where theres a fair amount of options to choose from whether youre looking for food or grooming supplies for a fish, dog, cat, or what have you. I found the employees to have been quite friendly and helpful in aiding me to find what I was looking for.
My dog has been getting groomed by Julie for over a year now and she really is the best!! I highly recommend her
I always love bringing my dog here to pick out his treats! The staff is always so lovely and very helpful
Knowledgable staff that are willing to help you find what You need !

The staff is amazing and so so sweet! I bring my dog Milo here every month for a groom and his groomer Aline is the SWEETEST. I used to take him all the way to Vancouver until I read great reviews on Aline and decided to try this location out as it is much closer to my house.
