One time I got confused about his appointment time (thought it was later) and she was super sweet and understanding through it all. Cant recommend her and this location enough.

Very Happy with my Experience. I came all the way from Langley to pick up my new puppy. Tonight I made it just in time before this Petsmart closed. The manager helped me find everything I needed to care for my new puppy and he made sure I got the essentials for my puppy. very helpful and my puppy is really happy with his treats and chew toys.

Tbis is an awesome petstore, I got a betta there and they check its water for free each time I take it there and they are knowlegeable in giving advice how I should take care of my fish. Good job! & Thank you.
Convenient place. A bit different to park but with a little patience you will find a spot. Nice employees. Some discounts for aquarium stuff are pretty good but you have to take chances.
Not too busy, staff know where everything is. Made my trip quick and easy.

Booked my dog in for training class since the one we usually go to was fully booked. Didnt really expect too much from it since most reviews about their classes arent that great, but I was pleasantly surprised at how great the trainor was. Our dog trainor was Irene and she was so pleasant to work with. She was always willing to answer our questions, give different suggestions and really cared about making sure we understood every topic and assisted us whenever we were struggling to do certain exercises with our dog. Overall a really great experience taking the class with her!
Our Cleos doggie wonderland! Everything you need for dogs and other pets. Reasonable priced, great staff.
Lots of products and very helpful staff. All was clean and animals looked well cared for. Got a beautiful fighter fish and his setup.

Sweetest staff, today I was struggling to pick up a kitty litter and this bearded buff staff member with the biggest smile on his face offered me a cart and lifted the 40lb litter with one arm like it was nothing! and put it In a cart he brought me. It was the first time anyone in any store has done that for me. Amazing job petsmart! Glad to be shopping here.
Awesome service, very friendly staff and impeccably clean store my dogs love it here.

Great job!! I really enjoyed the training  experience at Pet Smart. Marianna was a wonder Trainer, very patient, understanding and right in cue with correcting the dogs and giving suggestions. I was sad to hear she was moving out of province. Overall it was a great experience and I have gained confidence in teaching our dog. Overall it was a great experience, great value and I definitely recommend
Julie is an amazing professional and so friendly and we got a great grooming service there. Super satisfied with the service.

Very friendly staff, sometimes our pup gets too excited and he peed inside the store, we are so sorry about it but the staff handle it like it happens everyday(I believe so too ) They also have grooming and training service.

Always a pleasure to visit the pet smart store in Burnaby and on Lougheed hwy I have always been a satisfied pet Parent . When shopping for my furbaby they always have the most fabulous and up to date pet supplies to spoil your pets and take care of their well being
Super friendly staff at this location. Never had an issue. Their grooming services are usually very booked up, so I d recommend trying to book a couple weeks in advance

We love Mariana! My dogs and I have been taking classes here and we love it. Mariana uses only positive reinforcements and helps me understand my dogs better, she also is able to adapt to the needs of each dog and owner. We have been to a few different dog training schools and so far, this has been our favorite!

Hands down my doggie has one of the best groomers ( Suzanne) in the area! My furbaby has very high anxiety and she knows exactly what to do with him. She has this calming factor with him. I wouldnt bring him anywhere else! I would like to add, all groomers are extremely good! But since my dog is high matienence, he needs to be with the same person. If I had it my way, I would take him to anyone there!

Great customer service. I always order online and pick up. They messed up the order on the recent one where they only gave me 1 of each product instead of the multiples. But I went back the next day and they were super nice and helpful

The girls at the salon are incredible! I have a nervous pup who hates baths and Aline, his groomer, is super patient and loving towards him. Its Its great team and I appreciate what they do for my Loki
Very well organized, staff are always well mannered. We come here for our beardie needs

Really helpful staff. They really know their cat stuff. We asked them advice on what to get or try for our five month old kitty, and they made great suggestions. A bunch were cat owners themselves and shared their experience. And when certain treats didnt work out, they were easily returned and refunded. Very understanding.

I was planning to buy a fish but I don t have a lot of information about the fish types and how to take care of them. Then the staff person name Laura helped me a lot she has the knowledge about all the fishes and their food. And also how to take care of tank. Thank you so much Laura
They have a very large selection of cat treats, and a variety of cat food brands. Whenever I am in the area I would stop by this PetSmart to see what new items they have.
Very talented and caring staff. They always take good care of my buddy.

This location has a really quick turnaround for cat products since the store is centrally located by the biggest mall in BC and is a bit smaller in size. Staff are friendly and its quite easy to ask questions if you ever have any! If youre looking for clearance items (ie from holiday collections), you may not run into any luck here. Just as a heads up!
Pet Smart is a nice friendly store, and has everything I need for my pet. My dog likes going there too!

Petsmart is our usual spot to grab all our pet supplies. Staff are friendly but sometimes its hard to get served in the fish/reptile department. Some days it seems like no one is working the floor and we have to confront the front cashier to get someone. Other than that, we are happy with everything else. Store is generally always clean and maintained.

Amazing collection of fish. I do not have any other pet, but as far as fish is concerned, this is a one stop shop for me. I can stop by any time and walk away with the species I want. Not to mention they have a wide range of fish food, and other accessories as well.

Great store huge selection and great prices when theres sales, no pet adoption during covid but was told pet adoptions can still be applied for online. Aside from that there was plenty of fish and pet toys but hey its a pet store. The staff were very accommodating and helpful and especially ecstatic when I asked about adoption.

I was babysitting my Granddaughters Little Dog he didn t like the rain so so went to a pet smart for a raincoat I was told by the sales girl that they put them away we joked about maybe keeping them out because I dint realized the rainy season was winter so I was on my way out and the sales Gir named Eden came running up and had gone into the back and took the time to find a Jacket I thought it was extremely caring and nice to go out of her way Great Customer Service

Always love Jade for grooming my babies, and the staff very helpful and very kind even though is not full service pet store They always try give you the best as they can which is very understandable!!

I like petsmart for their selection of dog produces, whether its for food or toys or just anything that I need for my dog. Theyre also my go to for bird food for my budgies. The associates are always friendly and always there to help or answer any questions.
The store is well maintained and the staff are very friendly and helpful. Groomers are awesome! Our dog has always been looked after well and has had a perfect grooming session every time. Thank you!

This store has everything you need for your pet. We were choosing a scratching pole for our cat. They have lots of them already assembled and ready to use. We bought one and a cashier was very friendly and gave us advice about how to use it properly, so our cat would understand where she should do scratching. At home we put the scratching pole in front of our sofa, so the cat can see us watching her scratching and amazingly! - she started scratching it right away to please us! Thanks a lot for the pole and for the advice!
Great staff, always friendly and helpful, and I love all the cat products! I can always find something new and different here. I bought some cat calming spray and it really helped my cats chill out.
The worker at the front knew my son was autistic so she understood the position when we got to the front of store. Excellent customer service skill.

I am so pleased with Petsmart at Metrotown!  The staff are just amazing!  We take our pom Lola in often to get groomed, or to just get her nails done.  Lola was their very first client when they first opened up!  The staff are friendly, professional,  and extremely helpful!  Ive been a loyal customer for years,  because they do such a great job with Lola!  If you havent had the opportunity to take your four legged family member here, I highly recommend it!  I love this Petsmart!!

Ive been taking Bella here for about a year or so. She is a 13 year old chocolate lab. The groomer named Winter is the best... so gentle and patient with her, I always know shes in good hands! Thank you for being so wonderful!
Great place to grab affordable and good quality pet supplies. I also got both our family hamsters here. This location is always clean and well stocked.

The grooming staff are amazing! We brought our rescue chihuahua x miniature pinscher here for over a year since we first got her and they have always been so good to her. They even talked me through how to cut her nails myself when I told them we were moving out of province. They have always done a quick, and impeccable job clipping her nails and have even given us heads up when our vaccines are expiring. Ohana and I miss them so much already, especially after her last nail trim in a new grooming salon, which wasnt half as good as the girls here ever did!

The staff are really kind and especially the tall guy in the back [august] super friendly and helped so much he was very good at his job and i can tell he puts the safety of the animals first at all times! i will be buying all my pet supplies here. Thanks

Big store with lots of different products at reasonable prices. Staff are friendly, knowledgeable, and helpful. I come here to get everything for my cat. Considering buying a lizard or fish from them too.
Store manager at this store(Josh), is simply Awesome!! Very understanding about the concern I had while retuning an item.
We have our new Hammy from here.

Good nice people, relatively good selection for aquariums and well maintained fish and tanks. O was in other pet store for fish and there was 1-2 dead fish in almost every tank so I was afraid of buying from there.
Great customer service. Was able to find a lost receipt because I was a member
They always have everything I need for my 2 cats. Staff always have great advice when needed as well. Awesome loyalty programs for certain foods, helps cut down on cost. Love this place!!

I had to bring in my puppy to the Station Square location as the last location I went to failed to get her mats out and actually trim her down. I booked my appointment with Allison and she was excellent. She took very well of Mika, knowing the whole ordeal will most likely result with Mika being shaven down due to the severity of the mats. Mika got a fresh hairdo for the summer and definitely would come back to this location. Allison did a great job communicating/reassuring me with any changes need to be done. Thank you!

I took my dog Tony to Sarah at the Metrotown salon. Tony is a real mamas boy but she made him feel special and he allowed her to cut his hair and nails without biting her. this is always a plus as I do hate it when blood is drawn. However, she did a great job, he looks simply fab, and he is only slightly upset by the ordeal. Thank you Sarah. You are a groomer extraordinaire for my nervous little dog with extreme separation anxiety.
Burnaby station is great for grooming exactly opposite of Lougheed branch. we had really good experience for taking our dogs to this store.
They have very nice staff, I always go there for shopping although another Pet Smart location is near than this to me because I like it :)
The young Asian lady working here is very nice and kind. I would keep coming back to petsmart because I feel appreciated & valued as a customer.
the groomers have always been incredibly patient, kind, and enthusiastic to my dog and I since I was a kid to now bringing her in for her trims. I really appreciate it :)
I got great support and advice from Eddy, the sales associate. His recommendations when I got my new puppy was so helpful. I highly recommend this store.

A big shout out to Eddy !!! I went in today to get cat food and litter. I wrenched my lower back and was unable to bend down to lower shelf to get the tins I needed. Eddy was an Angel and also helped me with the litter !!! Many Thanks Again Eddy !!!
Alison is a fabulous groomer.  My dog loves her and always looks fantastic when she is done.  I would highly recommend Alison and her colleagues!
Amazing customer service. Been here several times in the last couple weeks and the staff has gone above and beyond to help me find everything I needed.
This is a great store. Made my first purchase today. The staff couldnt have been more helpful.
Best store for all kinds of things you might need for your beloved pets!
Associates were very friendly and polite. I found what I was looking for at a good price. I will be coming back.
Tess was amazing! I was adopting two baby rats and she recommended the right products and overall was really helpful.
Got some pet tags and dog toys from here. Great service! Always quiet which is nice as someone who has sensory issues.
Love this store and their exchange policy. Never let the customer down. One place where my oet is Welcome and cared for.
Like this place because I can come with my pet and she can shop by herself....also we take training for her.  Very good and friendly staff that always help ...
Good  lady was moody she shouldve stayed homr
Great staff! They helped me finding out what I needed.
Great place with cheap deals! Love the fish & birds.. really would like to get a gerbil 1 day from there too
Staff ensured to ask and help out customers find the products they need. Great customer service.
Love the store! Always happy experiences here.
Awesome shop. Any kind of food you imagine can be found here. Plus they let pets in, I like it because your pet can help you in choosing and it is fun !
Helpful staff, always find everything I need
Good location, parking could be issue many times.
Love this store. Super friendly and helpful staff. Always neat and tidy.
Easy to find, nice staff
Great staff and selection. Very knowledgeable. Nicole was an absolute joy and very helpful and went above and beyond.
Super friendly and helpful staff. Ive always had a really good experience at this location!
They have good variety of products for my reptiles and the animals they have are well taken care of
Always have had a good experience at this one (Station Square) Very friendly and helpful staff. Definitely recommend A++
Love this place. We get food and litter for our cat here. Great service and staff.
my favorite one. the one cashier, i did not get her name, is super knowledgeable, compassionate. thanks
The only place in Burnaby you can buy crickets! Super friendly and helpful staff. Clean and organized.
Best customer service ever receive by Nikki ( store manager ) I had a big problem with my fish tank and she help me a lot , thanks Nikki and thanks to your excelente team !!
One of my favorite places.
Everyone is friendly, kind and easy to talk with. I manage to find everything easily. Thank you.
Awesome place for products and information on looking after your pets and the staff are awesome and will answer all of your questions.
I get fish food there so it great and clean store and fast service
Our favourite pet smart to go to the grooming team is awesome, Andreanne did an amazing job. Thanks!

As with any business, some employees are great and some not so great, but the salon staff here are amazing. Ever since Stephanie took over as salon manager, the salon has become SO MUCH BETTER. My dog is reactive and Stephanie is the ONLY one she lets groom her - which she always does an amazing job! Its obvious that PetSmart as a corporation cares more about money and their customers than it does its employees, but I can tell that the salons priority is taking care of the pets and making them feel comfortable. I cant imagine having to deal with reactive dogs and rude customers everyday, but they do an amazing job.

Harley, Megan, Emily & Stephanie. Are awesome! My little guy always looks cute. Heres a pic, new hairdo, new bed, new food. The only thing, he is camera shy. Haha. Just a thought. Rbc is gone from the New Westminister Skytrain Station.  Lotsa room for PETSMART to take over. Would be great! So many of us, would find it more convenient.
The staff were all wonderful and so helpful. It was a treat to meet so many happy dogs shopping with their owners too!

I recently took my furry companion to PetSmart for a grooming session, and I m delighted to share my positive experience. The dog grooming service provided by PetSmart was exceptional in every way, from the care given to my pet to the professionalism of the groomers. Upon arrival, the staff welcomed us with a warm and friendly demeanor, immediately putting my dog at ease. The groomers demonstrated a genuine love for animals and a deep understanding of different breeds and their specific grooming needs.

Very friendly knowledgeable staff.  Bought a dwarf hamster into our family and did not realize its an escape artist.  Upgraded the cage and the staff was very friendly and helpful in exchanging the cage.  Went back to get more goods and staff have been very helpful

If you are going to get a cat or dog, fish or some reptile, its a perfect place to visit. At the same time, here you will find food for them, costumes, accessories, toys, and professional advice. Sometimes here are great discounts for aquariums and other stuff.
I love this store. Staff is always friendly.  Helpful too. Convenient location for me. Lots of parking space. Everything is good
We take our pup here for his nail trim and haircuts. The groomers are take great care and attention with him. Our favorite person to see is Stephanie B!

Great store, really really nice staff and fantastic management. They are so helpful and friendly every time Ive been in. Oh and the grooming department is so friendly. Duke & Digby LOVED them. They loved going in the store when they were little puppies and would ride in the carts :-)
Stephanie always provides our dog Panda with the best grooming experience!
Great location. They are well stocked and friendly always happy to help. Our dogs love visiting this location!!

This is one out of the few branches of PetSmart in Burnaby/Vancouver area, and it has been the best one so far. I have been here for dog food, dog tags, salon and fishes, and their service has been top quality all the time. As long as you tell them what you want clearly, they will for sure help you. Physical environment is spacious, clean and organized, easy to find what you are looking for. Pets allowed inside. Parking is not a problem. Highly recommend this branch.

I am so grateful for the staff making it a possibility to edit my Uber delivery  for something I can t get delivered. I am super sick and contagious, and really needed this delivery done for my pets! Thank you!!

Everything you could possibly need for almost any pet.  The employees are friendly, knowledgeable and love animals. We have purchased both Guinea Pigs and Chinchillas here and they obviously get handled often by employees, because they are much better socialized than animals we have bought from another local pet store.  The prices are great, and the selection is good too.  Watch out for sales because there are some amazing deals. And I love the customer rewards program. I basically just got a bag of hay for free because of the rewards program.

We had our Bouvier in for grooming.  She s a big goofy bouncy dog and can be a challenge. Leah did a phenomenal job and we love the cut.  We will be bringing our doggo back to this location every time.
Praise Rachel D. for a soft, healthy and tapered full groom look for my two dogs.  They are happy

Weve been coming here since we got out pup. Lisa, out trainer, has been great. The groomers are amazing I will never understand how they remember so many dogs their names etc. A little overpriced on some things but you can catch a great deal here and there. The training is definitely worth it for puppy socialization and the coupons they give as part of it. (Close to pays for half the training) its just a store in the end but youll never find a group of people so happy to welcome your pet to the store and I think thats why we keep going back.
Just purchased two skinny pigs. Staff were helpful during the process. I also bring our big fur baby here (pyrenees) to the groomer and they always do such a great job!

We took our puppy in for his first ever grooming and we were very nervous about whether he would have a good time. Our groomer, Kailee, absolutely knocked our socks off with how fantastic and comforting she was! She treated our puppy as her own and he had such a great time with her having a bath, getting his face and nails trimmed, having his ears cleaned, and having his paw pads shaved. She also went above and beyond our expectations and completely brushed away all his matted hair (he had a lot)! We will definitely be visiting Kailee again!
I couldn t find one of the items I was looking for and the staff were VERY helpful and cheerful. Always have great service here.
Always been a lovely place to groom my dog! Especially as he ages into his senior years
As usual great selection staff and very clean store. Friendly and you know what you sell in and out . Thank-you merry christmas

Saw a guy shoplifting here. Told a staff member that some one had stolen something by stuffing it down there pants. The staff member didn t care at all, and no cameras are present there. Seems to me like pet smart is ok with you stealing from it. 5/5 stars for five finger discounts.
staff is very friendly and helpful. I bought quite a lot, she helped to get a cart for me since its a little big too much to carry with hands. Im happy with the experience
Got both my cats a haircut here.  They did a great job of it. Wish they would carry the brand of food I feed them.

A large store with a corner store feel. Staff are very friendly, knowledgeable and helpful. Pet training is top notch and the groomers do very good work. A wide variety of pet products that staff match with your pets need. Simply my dogs favorite place.

Michelle is the nicest and friendliness gal. Randomly greeting people any time she was in the area and just so kind to chat as much as people want. Also very knowledgeable and helped me a lot and kept coming back to check in with me.
Great PetSmart with fantastic service. I always go here for getting our dogs nails cut. Staff is very friendly and always eager to help.

I took my senior dog, Lily, to get groomed. She has only been professionally groomed once before when she was much younger.  Her groomer and stylist, Harley, was lovely and took all of my requests to heart. When I picked Lily up she was stunning. She looked 10 years younger.  You might say Harley did too good of a job because now when we go to the park all the young dogs cant stop following Lily around.  Shes too cute!! Thank you Petsmart and Harley for doing such a great job in a clean and bright facility.
The groomers here are great.  Sarboni always does a fabulous job with our dog.  Bridget runs a training course for dogs that is just outstanding and I cannot recommend her enough.  Great location.

I always found what I want there. All staffs are friendly and knowledgeable. When on sale, they actually have the best deal in town. Dont know much about dog food, but fish food yeah for sure. My puffer only like a very specific dried food, which is the shrimp/catfish sticks, and only Petsmart carries that type of food.

I took my two Pomeranians (Meka/Hanlon) in today. The two girls that worked on them did such a terrific wonderful job. They were incredibly nice, gentle, and beautiful in spirit. I cannot say enough of how happy I was of how they treated my dogs and me.  Definitely will be returning on a regular basis.

Everybody in the store is so welcoming and friendly and accommodating. I went there today and bought a pet  stroller  and were strongly about it . Our two little dogs absolutely love it and our kids also have huge smiles on their faces.  We would like thank everyone  for  Creating a very happy family memory.

Very clean and well organized store. The employees were excellent. As soon as the lineup started to grow, the employees opened up more tills so there was no waiting. The employees were extremely friendly, helpful, and efficient.

Thank you Sheree. I so appreciated your warm personality and you did a wonderful job clipping Sweeties paw nails. Sweetie really liked you so I know she was in good hands. I also greatly appreciated the help carrying my kitty to and from the store. That was really customer service! Well be back.

There is an absolutely lovely employee who helped us today, she is the tall Caucasian female with short brown hair/glasses. Her service is beyond exceptional and very helpful. Please give this lady a raise! I will be shopping here often. Great store!

A male staff member helped to locate a bag of dry cat food which was emptied on the shelf. He looked in the stock room and eventually he found it on the pile of variety of pet foods which was higher than my height. Well done Petsmart!!

I came in with no appointment and the store was extremely busy however I was well looked after by everybody and Barbara found time to check my little puppy in for a shampoo and haircut and Stephanie did an exceptional job making sure that my five-month-old puppy was looked after. I was very impressed and did not expect this type of exceptional extended service and was delighted to receive five star service which obviously deserves a five star review.
Clean and staff are very friendly and have an excellent repore with pets and owners Always pleased with grooming My groomer Stephanie is awesome
Very neat and organized store. You can say hi to birdies, kitties and other pets who are waiting to find a home. You can buy different brands of pet food and supplies.

Grooming staff is super friendly and I feel comfortable leaving my dog with them for an haircut. Make sure you call in to book an appointment. Because they are usually full for walk in. Price is also very reasonable.
Good inventory compared to other locations. Outside of busy hours and may have to wait for staff to unlock fridge/freezer for frozen food.

I am never disappointed with the friendly and professional service that I receive at this location.   Today Harjit helped me with a difficulty that I had,and that reflects every time I have asked for help from any staff member.   Keep up the good work!

I happened to do a walk in today just to get my dogs nails clipped and the front desk were super accommodating. I then asked about approx book ins for a wash and she said they could take him in right away! Dropped him off just after 2pm and got him back extra fresh just after 330! When I picked maverick up all the girls were saying such great things about him and maverick looks so nice and clean! We love going into the marine location, every person we come in contact with there is always so accompanying and friendly! Thanks to Harley for writing the cutest pawgress report card!! We ll see you guys soon! :)

I feel bad because I can t remember what her name was but when I went there the girl working by the fish was literally the sweetest! You can tell she absolutely loves the animals living there and takes very good care of them.
Good collection of fish. Would have loved to buy bettas (which they didn t have in their stock at that time), but will definitely go back.

I went to buy a fish tank and a pet fish, first time buyer, a gift for my daughter. Petsmart BigBend Burnaby I was extremely fortunate to be helped out by  Sraboni and Harjit.  They took the time to explain all the things we required and were very knowledgeable. Employees who demonstrate this kind of superior service are hard to come by.  I thank you for your kindness and excellence in customer service!

Great selection of pet food and supplies.  Fridge with raw food and packaged bones.  Great selection of fish, aquadic plants & snails.  Really good aquarium selection & supplies.  Good return and exchange policies.
We get buggos for our Bubbles (a beardie). Staff here (especially Michelle) are always pleasant!

Brought my dog for bath and she was warmly cared for. The staff was very friendly and walked me through how its done since it was our first visit. One area for improvement is that the grooming room is a bit smelly and the air is filled with allergen. I couldnt stop sneezing for the rest of the day after only spent a few minutes in there. The friendly people that work there definitely can use a better working environment. Special callout to Kailee who is very friendly and caring, she really took the time and gave my pet a great groom.
I went to buy a water filter for our aquarium.. The staff are very friendly and knowledgeable.. The store was clean and well stocked. Overall a great experience
Staff are very friendly. Grooming staff are very good at remembering the pets. Always greet Munky with a smile and a rub. Been using them for 10+ years and will continue to go back. A+++ service.
Took my dog here to get nails trimmed for the first time and I was very impressed with the grooming department inside. The ladies were very comforting when I let them take my Tony.
Great products and pets here.
Very friendly, helpful staff! Harjit was especially helpful in getting enough crickets together for my bearded dragon, even though the tank was running low, which my pet will definitely appreciate!
I have been taking my 9 year old Bernese to Petsmart since he was a puppy. I love the friendly, knowledgeable staff and my dog loves them too! He always looks great after his grooming session.
As usual, friendly and helpful staff. Stock is slightly better than other stores but still many empty shelves.
Harjit provided me with great customer service. I was getting a dog airport carrier for my pooch sure everything was complete and no parts were missing. Very knowledgeable. Will definitely come back

A great big layout, and super well organized, making finding what you came for very simple. Their system is very up-to-date about recalled items so you dont take anything dangerous home to your furbabies.

The girls on staff are very attentive! As soon as I walked in a customer service representative guided me to the thunder shirts and helped me pick out the perfect size for my baby girl Maltese MILA! I tried the thunder shirt on her and it fits perfectly! Also she calmed down a lot from how she was before! Mila would bark at every sound and go crazy whenever anyone came by. Now she only barks when someone is at the door and as soon as we answer the door and she settles back down again and sits quietly!  I give her a treat when she behaves properly to help re-enforce a job well done!

I did on online order on pet supplies on discount for Canada Day long weekend and for some reason the system messed up the order and sent one item for a pick up at another PetSmart location. Carolyn at the PetSmart Marine Drive was really helpful when we realized the screw up and let me get the item from her store, called the other location, canceled that one item order for me and arranged for them to refund me that item. Carolyn gets these 5 stars just for her very helpful, polite and amazing customer service.
i only have a few fishes. not sure about other things but they have a very good policy for fish and seems like its maintained pretty good. fish supplies that i need are always in stock

They were closing and I need something urgently and they looked after me despite the fact they stayed open for another 20 minutes and I was the only customer in the store. I really appreciate that type of extended service and did not expect it. I m sure this is not a regular occurrence but I wanted to post a nice review reflecting the great service that I received.

They always have food in stock and usually on sale. You may have to find things yourself as it usually takes a while to get help from staff unless you go straight to the register. I come here to get my Golden Retrievers grooming done. He gets the pawdicure (ear cleaning, tooth brushing, nail grinding and fur trim around the paws). We ask for Jess! Benji loves coming to see her
If you want to give your pet PREMIUM food, come to this place. Its expensive food but yr pet will benefit. No fillers or GMO. We buy TIKI CAT cat food here. Member discounts and incentives available.

Kailee is awesome with my dog Pickles! It usually takes more than 3 hours to just get Pickles bathed and haircut done (sometime Pickles struggled so much the haircut and hair dry could only be half done.) Kailee did all the bathing, teeth brushing, haircut, and nail trimming in 2.5 hours which really surprised me!
Always a pleasure getting Albi groomed by Stephanie B She has earned his trust, which is amazing!! Thank you

Clean and friendly store with lots of inventory. A staple for my dogs necessities from food, toys, snacks, leashes and salon. Also great stock of essentials for small reptiles and bird. Lots of parking and they have stores next to them that allow dogs to go in.
Love how they have cats for adoption. They seem to treat them so nice.
Would absolutely recommend their pet grooming services. Went in for a nail trim for my cat and to mention she is a feisty little one. Barbara and her team were patient and did an awesome job.
I take my Australian shepherd here for a trim, he is always nervous but by the end I can barely get him out of the store. They take wonderful care of him here every time.

Hargit and her staff are amazing..they helped us find everything...where are the blue worms- just over here..our little chihuahua had a pee accident..- heres the pee station if you need any help just call...and they were all so kind ..thanks for the great experience
Friendly staff lots of stock

While I was shopping yesterday I saw 3 different dogs (it was around 3 or 330 a papillon, toy poodle, and maltese mix)  come out of grooming looking stunning, happy, and fabulous! The folks in grooming work hard and it shows
They have a dog washing area. For $10, you get shampoo, towels, and dryer.
My favourite PetSmart location. Grooming salon is top notch for the price and great friendly staff
Great selection of fish with reasonable pricing. They warranty is also amazing. If a fish dies in a months time you can bring it back to exchange

I cant say enough good things about the groomers here! Jas ALWAYS takes such good care of my 5 1/2 year old schnauzer Abby. They are such friendly ladies and I love how they greet Abby and I. They tell me honestly how she was and Ive kept all her Pawgres report cards. I even bake the gals cookies at Christmas and will give them all Starbucks cards to let them know how much I appreciate their hard work. See you in 6 weeks ladies!

Our big boy Dallas is not a fan of strangers (big, muscly mastiff rottweiler cross) but everytime he comes to the groomers here he is generally calm and gets groomed without incident. I heard the groomers talking to the dogs in a soothing voice and man it shows how much they care. Best wash and nail cut I have tried, Dallas always feels very snuggable afterwards and gets a complimentary handkerchief on the neck and a smile on the face.
The best part except all the obvious things, this location is quite and still well stocked. Plenty of room if you want to being your pet here with you
Max got really dirty after playing in the dog park! Tiana did an awesome job giving Max a bath and brushing. He looks like his awesome self again! What a difference! Thanks guys!!!

Very friendly staff, my dog was freaking out from the floor being slippery and the cashier was very nice to her and helping her calm down
Good selection and usually good sale prices on somd items. Friendly and helpful staff. Big store, bright lighting.
Excellent atmosphere   and customer service
Super friendly place.  Always found the staff very helpful, especially if I looked lost and confused.  Wide selection to choose from.
The staff are great and obviously pet people. We are doing the puppy training class and Lisa is amazing. Would recommend!
Despite being a big box store, the staff is friendly and knowledgeable.  The store is very well-stocked and arranged well.  This is my go-to place for pet supplies.
Andrea was amazing! She spent so much time and was very patient with finding the right harness for my dog.
Julian was knowledgeable, friendly and courteous. Made the whole shopping experience pleasurable and memorable. Kudos to Julian!
Jas is amazing! The grooming staff in general are great!

I feel very grateful for this Petsmart location for the way they take care of their little critters. I have visited most Petsmarts in the lower mainland and I often saw little hamsters and mice running on wheels that are not only dirty but also way too small for them (it would hurt their spines). And they often lived in smelly cages (pee soaked bedding) and having only pellets (no nutrients) for food. But this Petsmart in North Vancouver provide their rodents with proper size(bigger) and clean wheels to run on, their beddings are clean, and they even give them a variety of fresh vegetables for snacks alongside pellets! I saw happy and healthy  mice exercising on the wheels and comfortably cuddling with each other today. They were so comfortable with humans(thanks to the kind people who take good care of them) they would come out and curiously sniff us. I m so happy for the animals to be taken such good care of. Thank you guys so much NV Petsmart!
We do our Yorkie grooming at PetSmart. We tried several groomers and we have settled on PetSmart for good service and value.
Great service and always make my dog feel special. Staff always helpful friendly and obviously love animals.

Hi, I had my dog in for a grooming today and I am really really really happy with the results. I got an early morning appointment at 8:15 AM so she was the first one in the door. I asked for an especially thorough de-shedding, and I can t be happier with the results. I even took her into the park just to do a quick brushing after and I barely can get anything off of her. Will definitely use Petsmart grooming from now on.
Great selection and friendly staff. I am happiest when o don t see pets up for adoption there   but If it is a good spot where they can be shown and adopted to good homes  that can t be bad.

Normally I dont write reviews for basic retail locations, but last week I felt the employees really went above and beyond to help me get a dog tag ring onto a collar. The woman at the cashier spent her spare moments, between helping customers at the till, with focused determination to get the dog tag on the collar for me. It probably took 15 minutes total but she got it on there when Im pretty sure theres no chance I ever could have. Whenever I go into this location, the staff are cheerful and very helpful.

I just want to thank the staff for being so kind. Coco was hit by a car, and she needed a special harness so I can help her walk and rehabilitate. The staff was super understanding of the situation and went above and beyond to help me. Thank you so much! You are really one of a kind.
They helped me get the kitty liter in my car. Outstanding service
The staff is very friendly and helpful. They helped me find the brand I was looking for.
Your pet store to go! Good collection for cats and dogs and other animals. Friendly staff! They got some new kittens as well.

I have a difficult Westie to groom - he hates having his feet touched -  and I am also very fussy about the cut he gets. Dariane at North Vancouver Petsmart is great on both accounts. She is very responsive to any suggestions I make (e,g, tail a bit shorter) and the price is very good.
I got my beautiful long haired syrian here. The lady who helped us with the hammies was alright but the cashier was really kind.
My betta fish was sick and one of the staff members (unfortunately I can t remember his name) patiently explained what i have to do for the fish. The fish is healthy and happy now

The grooming salon excelled today with my pug Mac. He now has a lovely soft coat, very little shedding, and is a very happy boy with his trimmed nails. Thankyou groomers, plus you always give us a great welcome
This is essentially our zoo on the way home from school. From skinny pigs (hairless guinea pigs) to fancy mice, we love holding them all.

I love this store! Nice selection of any pet foods. Staff members are really friendly. We took our dog for training. The session was 6 weeks long and Derrick - the trainer - did an amazing job! Highly recommended to everyone who need some help or simply if you need food  or accessories to your pet.

As always, great grooming and care provided for our puppy! Rachel and Isabel offered suggestions on how we can do some things at home to improve our dogs health and future grooming experiences. Feedback was welcomed, and very on point.
Had what I needed, helped with my questions and were very friendly

Ive been popping into this north van location for a few weeks now expanding my new aquarium hobby and I have found the staff here to be very knowledgeable in their area extremely kind and helpful and unlike some pet stores I have been to in the past they actually care about their animals when I first got started they wouldnt allow me to buy a new fish until they had done their very best to ensure I had everything in order to keep happy fishies including a set up check as well as a water sample test they direct me to the proper foods and have taught me how to care for my.individual fish Breeds I now have 15 fish 2 frogs 2 eels all living happily in their community tanks with their own feeding schedules and specific foods and feeding schedules I can honestly say I wouldnt have figured out half of what I now know without them and would have killed more than a few of my gill babies in trying to figure it all out on my own they have helped me create my own little ecosystems all working in partnerships to maintain their tanks 10/10 would recommend

Dee took such good care of my little pup! She is patient, thorough and gentle with the doggies!! I definitely recommend her if youre thinking of getting your dog groomed here. Her customer service was impeccable too!!!

Theyve got everything you need for your favourite critter!  Service is friendly, lots of selection. The new Pet Perks program is pretty good too, doesnt take long to get some cash back.  Grooming service is decent too. Bonus points for the great dog walk area (Harbourview Park) with a trail beginning directly behind PetSmart.. walk under the train bridge towards the water!

I love this location. It s never too busy and I ve been on very different times during the day and night. They have a great selection of pet foods toys beds and they also have cute adorable cats and kittens available for adoption which you can view. My cat only eats the Nutrience brand of food and only Petsmart seems to carry it and I usually get a 10% discount since I continue to buy it. I love this location the staff are also very friendly and helpful!

My go to pet store now that Pet Boutique has shut down. Store is very clean and has a wide variety of supplies for almost any animal. I go there for bedding for my snake primarily but also have purchased fish, hamsters, and birds from them in the past. Overall, its a great store with a fantastic and friendly staff.

My dogs love this place and the team is so good to them. The grooming services are spectacular. They ve got all the necessary treats and toys... it s like pet Disneyland. At checkout the register automatically promts me with the opportunity to donate to the PetSmart foundation. This group has funded almost every no-kill shelter and SPCA built in Canada. I appreciate a brand that actually cares. I can t see myself shopping anywhere else.
Excellent lost my wallet in parking lot and staff had it when I called in Thank God there is honest people still in the world

I had an issue with online ordering which resulted in my having to purchase a product I didnt really want.  When I got to the store the product I wanted was on the shelf.  The cashier, very  cheerfully, processed the return of the wrong product and billed me for the correct product.  Problem solved.  Staff at Abbotsford store always exemplary.
This is our cats favorite store! Always has her favorite food and treats in stock. Also, with doordash, you can get your supplies delivered for free at home. Highly recommend.

I had lots of bad experiences for grooming before, but yesterday Dee did a very clean and nice job with my little boy. She was super nice and I loved a little report card she made for Tipsy. Thank you for your service.

Very nice selection of fish tanks and tank ornaments :) the staff where very friendly as well   . . . . I felt bad for the Siamese fighting fish in the small plastic cups barely moving, theres no way thats okay or right in any way  .

This location is very clean and well organised. All the staff wear face coverings. Wide selection of pet supplies and food and there is a dog grooming department in the store. No cat adoptions at the moment, hope they return as that is always a highlight of our visit and where we got our cat.

This is a pet store.  I like turtles.  I like turtles a lot.  At this store they have various pet store related things.  I do not get spooked when I go to this store.  The opposite.  This is primarily because it is well known that animals do not have ghosts, so it is impossible for this store to be haunted.  Please remember this, and you too shall not be spooked.

This PetSmart has the friendliest and most knowledgeable staff I have met in a pet store ever. The girl who helped me had a 4 year old hamster and seemed to know what he was doing. I do quite a bit of research on hamsters  and it was really great that they know what they are doing there. Thank you pet smart!
Love me some guinea pig visits whenever I get my own guinea pig food.  Great service. Parking lot is maintained. Easy entrance and exit.  Go here now for cool pet times.

Fantastic Customer Service. My daughters hamster got sick 2 weeks after we bought it and the store gladly took it back, had a vet look at it and promised to treat it with medication if possible. They did it all with empathy and kindness as my 10 year old was in tears due to its recent turn for the worse. Regardless of what the final outcome is, I will purchase any future pets from this store as they stand by their products.
Rebecca is super friendly, helpful and knowledgeable and got my dogs on food that doesnt make them itchy or disinterested. They love mealtime now. Im a customer for life, thanks Rebecca.

I dont often go to PetSmart but they carry the kitty litter my cat likes for the best price.  My experience in the past has been ok but this time was particularly good. There were plenty of sales staff available if you had questions.  Also unlike some pet stores they were adopting out adult animals.  They have also added free delivery on purchases over $50 in the area!

Everything youll want for your pets needs is there. Friendly staff. Probably dont need mention this but pets are welcome to shop with you. I like how they have toys at dog height. My dog was able to pick his own toy!

This is West Vancouver s new premier destination for all of your pet supply needs.  Bravo PetSmart!
